net.sourceforge.metware.binche
Class BiNChENode

java.lang.Object
  net.sourceforge.metware.binche.BiNChENode

public class BiNChENode
extends Object

This class is used to represent each of the nodes produced by the enrichment analysis, containing p-value and other indicators of the level of enrichment on the node.

Author:
Pablo Moreno

BiNChENode

public BiNChENode(Double pValue,
                  Double corrPValue,
                  Integer bigX,
                  Integer bigN,
                  Integer smallX,
                  Integer smallN,
                  String identifier)
Constructor for a ChEBI Node, which is the main object in the graph produced as result.

Parameters:
pValue - The p-value for the enrichment on this node, before any FDR correction.
corrPValue - The p-value of the enrichment on this node, after FDR correction.
bigX - The number of total entities on the given sample.
bigN - The number of total entities on the complete population.
smallX - The number of entities of the sample that fall in (or are children of) this node of the ontology.
smallN - The number of entities of the complete population that fall in (or are children of) this node of the ontology.
identifier - The identitifier for this node of the ontology.
